<!-- GLORIA -->
<section class="lib-gloria">
  <div class="lib-gloria-inner">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="rubric">She Is Not a Footnote to His Page</div>
      <p class="lede">Before he was a name on the docket, he was a name she said every day.</p>
      <h2 class="lib-gloria-name" aria-label="Gloria">
        Gloria.
        <span class="it">His mother.</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="role">
        She matters &mdash;
        <em class="gold">in her own right.</em>
        <em>Not because she lost him. Because she raised him.</em>
        <em>And because she is still here, asking.</em>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="lib-gloria-card reveal">
      <div class="label">A Vow to Gloria</div>
      <h3>What the Enclave promises his mother.</h3>
      <p>That we will say her son&rsquo;s name &mdash; in full, in print, without the qualifiers the state likes to attach.</p>
      <p>That we will say <em>her</em> name when we say his. That a mother who outlives her child is not a witness to a story; she is the <em>author</em> of it.</p>
      <p>That we will not publish about him without her blessing. That the page is hers to amend, to add to, to grieve through &mdash; and ours to keep, in her name, for as long as the lineage keeps records.</p>
      <dl class="vow">
        <div class="row"><dt>Filed for</dt><dd>Gloria Kenon</dd></div>
        <div class="row"><dt>In honor of</dt><dd>Her son, Tamion</dd></div>
        <div class="row"><dt>Held by</dt><dd>The Enclave, in trust</dd></div>
        <div class="row"><dt>For</dt><dd>As long as we are here</dd></div>
      </dl>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ASKS -->
<section class="lib-asks">
  <div class="lib-asks-head">
    <div class="lhs reveal">
      <span class="rubric">Five Asks · Plainly Stated</span>
      <h2>What the lineage <em>requires</em> of the county.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="rhs reveal">
      A libation does not replace an answer. It accompanies one. These are the items the Enclave will track on Tamion&rsquo;s page until they are met &mdash; one by one, in writing, by name.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="lib-asks-list reveal">
    <div class="lib-ask-row">
      <div class="num">i.</div>
      <div class="head">A full, independent autopsy &mdash; released to the family.</div>
      <div class="body">Not a summary. Not a press line. The complete report, in the family&rsquo;s hands, before it is in any other hands. <em>Gloria reads it first.</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="lib-ask-row">
      <div class="num">ii.</div>
      <div class="head">The custody timeline, hour by hour, named officer by named officer.</div>
      <div class="body">Who was working. Who saw him last. When the last cell check was logged. When the next one was. The county already has this. The family does not. <em>The gap is the asking.</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="lib-ask-row">
      <div class="num">iii.</div>
      <div class="head">The full video. Unedited. Released.</div>
      <div class="body">Whatever cameras exist &mdash; intake, hallway, cell-block. If a camera was off or covered, that fact is itself a finding. <em>An empty frame is an answer.</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="lib-ask-row">
      <div class="num">iv.</div>
      <div class="head">The medical record from booking forward.</div>
      <div class="body">Every intake screening, every requested medication, every flag raised by Tamion or anyone else. What was asked. What was answered. What was filed. What was not.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="lib-ask-row">
      <div class="num">v.</div>
      <div class="head">A standing review of every in-custody death in Fort Bend County, made public.</div>
      <div class="body">Tamion&rsquo;s name does not stand alone. A county that loses people in its cells owes the lineage an audit, in plain language, on a public page. <em>Names. Dates. Findings. Outcomes.</em></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

